    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">People</h2>
          <p><a href="https://kubernetes.io/blog/2020/03/19/join-sig-scalability/">Join SIG Scalability and Learn Kubernetes the Hard Way</a><br />
            &ldquo;Contributing to SIG Scalability is a great way to learn Kubernetes in all its depth and breadth, and the team would love to have you join as a contributor. I took a look at the value of learning the hard way and interviewed the current SIG chairs to give you an idea of what contribution feels like.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.cnn.com/2020/03/19/us/fastest-supercomputer-coronavirus-scn-trnd/index.html">The world&rsquo;s fastest supercomputer identified chemicals that could stop coronavirus from spreading, a crucial step toward a treatment</a><br />
            &ldquo;Summit, IBM&rsquo;s supercomputer equipped with the &lsquo;brain of AI,&rsquo; ran thousands of simulations to analyze which drug compounds might effectively stop the virus from infecting host cells.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://hbr.org/2020/03/do-your-di-efforts-include-people-with-disabilities">Do Your D&amp;I Efforts Include People with Disabilities?</a><br />
            &ldquo;Although 90% of companies claim to prioritize diversity, only 4% consider disability in those initiatives&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.diffblue.com/Education/research_papers/2019-diffblue-developer-survey/?utm_source=newsletter&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_campaign=DevOpsIsh">The Diffblue Developer Survey</a><br />
            What&rsquo;s wrong with software speed, quality, and cost? Oxford-based AI company Diffblue surveyed 300 developers to find out what the people who actually work with code have to say about testing, their pain points, and what&rsquo;s holding back DevOps in their organizations. <em>SPONSORED</em></p>

          <p><a href="https://d2iq.com/blog/d2iq-leadership-update">D2iQ Leadership Update</a><br />
            &ldquo;Tobi Knaup, co-founder and current CTO, will share the helm with William Freiberg, current President and COO, as Co-CEO&rsquo;s for D2iQ.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://peopleofcolorintech.com/articles/not-all-diverse-hiring-is-created-equal/">Not All Diverse Hiring Is Created Equal</a><br />
            &ldquo;As with anyone who exists in a space of privilege, I have a responsibility to use my privilege to benefit others. But given that I am also a diverse individual, how can I do this successfully? Here are three things I&rsquo;ve done, and will continue to do, with my unique position as a palatable diverse person in tech.&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
