    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">Process</h2>
          <p><a href="https://lwn.net/SubscriberLink/815137/fb7bca4bc7bf5f0b/">Bringing encryption restrictions in through the back door</a><br />
            &ldquo;EARN IT for short, is an attempt to force online service providers (e.g. Facebook, Google, etc.) to follow a set of &lsquo;best practices&rsquo; determined by a commission, to combat the scourge of CSAM; the composition of that commission makes it clear that end-to-end encryption will not be one of those practices, but companies that do not follow the best practices will lose liability protection for their users&rsquo; actions. It is, in brief, an attempt to force providers to either abandon true end-to-end encryption or face ruinous lawsuits—all without &lsquo;seeming&rsquo; to be about encryption at all.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://aminuteonthemic.com/episodes/episode4/">A Minute on the Mic: DevOps Meaning</a><br />
            &ldquo;Here&rsquo;s the 4th episode of A Minute on the Mic! Our question this round is &lsquo;What does DevOps mean to you?&rsquo;&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://tailscale.com/blog/how-tailscale-works/">How Tailscale works</a><br />
            I installed Tailscale this week on several systems. It&rsquo;s a dead-simple WireGuard VPN implementation. I am a little wary of it, but it is handy to have &lsquo;direct&rsquo; access to systems from anywhere. If installing WireGuard on everything were this easy, I&rsquo;d have done it already.</p>

          <p><a href="https://devopsi.sh/production-ready-c00e9">Checklist for building production-ready Kubernetes clusters</a><br />
            Like any aspiring Kubernaut, you&rsquo;ve been building Kube clusters in a dev/test environment for months. But now it&rsquo;s time to flip the switch and move your baby into production so the masses can reach your services. How do you know you&rsquo;ve set things up correctly and it&rsquo;s safe to launch into prod? Check out StackRox&rsquo;s checklist to help you prepare your containers and Kube clusters for production traffic. <em>SPONSORED</em></p>

          <p><a href="https://www.techrepublic.com/article/how-to-create-a-kubernetes-security-policy/">How to create a Kubernetes security policy</a><br />
            &ldquo;If you&rsquo;re looking to take your Kubernetes security to the next level, you&rsquo;ll want to start working with pod security policies. Here&rsquo;s a quick introduction to this feature.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://blocksandfiles.com/2020/03/20/netapp-nks-and-cloud-volumes-on-hci/">NetApp cans Kubernetes and Cloud Volumes services on HCI. But what is waiting in the wings?</a><br />
            NetApp promises something cool that provides more value. Uh huh&hellip;</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>

